  <datafield tag="545" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Harold T. Shapiro served as president of the University of Michigan from 1980 to 1987.</subfield>
    <subfield code="b">Shapiro's presidency endured a severe fiscal crisis that led to budget reductions and stringent reviews and evaluations of several schools and programs. Enhanced fundraising, including the Campaign for Michigan, aimed to reduce deficits. Other initiatives included efforts to increase minority student enrollment, recruitment and retention of minority faculty, and construction of a replacement hospital.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
